South Africa's Largest Mineworkers Union Considering National Mourning Day

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-04-14T08:45:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/south-africa-s-largest-mineworkers-union-considering-national-mourning-day.html
South Africa ’s National Union of
Mineworkers, the industry’s largest workers group, is
considering holding a national day of mourning “after the death
of two more workers,” it said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
